(Description)
Given the root of a binary tree, return the preorder traversal of its nodes' values.

--- Solution ---
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> preorderTraversal(TreeNode root) {
        List<Integer> preorder = new ArrayList<>();
        pre(root, preorder);
        return preorder;
    }

    private void pre(TreeNode root, List<Integer> result) {
        if (root == null)
            return;

        result.add(root.val);
        pre(root.left, result);
        pre(root.right, result);
    }
}

--- Approach ---
#Key Concept
The algolithmn was included two main parts.
1. Traversal followed by preorder rule.
2. Adding the values of preorder.

To add the values, I made a void function in the class level.
And under that function, traversal was worked.

In the traversal,
- Base case was when the root was null.
- Becasue the preorder is ordered by root - left - right, I added the value of binary tree at first,
  calling the recursion in order of left and right.
